In 1948, Truman was not on the ballot in Alabama; the Democratic column represents a Dixiecrat slate. We copy the third-party votes to the D_votes column to reflect that this still indicates a Democratic-leaning outcome.

Voters in Alabama voted for electors individually, with 5 pledged to Kennedy (D) and 6 unpledged; we count D_votes and T_votes based on the highest vote-getting elector in each category, as Wikipedia does.
NE-01 is the only electoral unit which had a more democratic raw margin compared to 2020. This is likely due in part to the redrawing of the district to include more of Omaha's suburbs.
